<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4607737>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. (A) Three new meiofaunal solenogaster species from Reid Rock, Friday Harbor: Ms, Macellomenia schanderi; Mm, Macellomenia morseae; Hs, Hypomenia sanjuanensis; note the similar size, colour, and body shape. Scale bar 1 mm; (B) posterior body end of M. schanderi showing: asp, abdominal spicules. Scale bar 150 µm; (C, D) epidermal sclerites of H. sanjuanensis sp. nov., light micrographs, polarized filter; (C) note the criss-cross arrangement of sclerites (cuticle removed with household bleach); scale bar 50 µm; (D) sclerite types: a, dorsolateral sclerites are acicular with small or almost reduced cavity, often serrated; b, most anterior sclerites are recurved and serrated; c, ventral scales; d, ventral scales found close to the pallial cavity opening; scale bar: 50 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4607737/files/figure.png" .

