<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4607746>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 6. Light micrographs of histological cross sections through various body regions of Macellomenia morseae. Scale bars 100 µm. (A) Anterior body end with atrium (a) showing atrial papillae; cu: cuticle; (B) radular region with radula (r) in the pharynx, cerebral ganglion (cer), and pedal pit (pp); the insert shows the radular apparatus in higher magnification; (C) section posterior to B with dorsal caecum of midgut (mg), oesophagus (es), lateroventral foregut glands (fgl), radular sheath (rs), pedal glands (pgl), and foot (f); (D) posterior body with pericardium (pc), hind gut (hg), and unpaired spawning duct (spd)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4607746/files/figure.png" .

